<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-80-0502 </DOCNO><TEXT>The reconversion of the Berlin gas utilities from town gas into naturalgas is assumed to be taking four phases until its completion in the 90s.The paper discusses a number of building measures required for the realizationof the natural gas project: 1. The already erected Berlin-Buckow naturalgas off-take, 2. the modification of the two gas systems' high-pressurelight gasoline cracking systems converting natural gas into town gasbefore it is being used, 3. the installation of underground natural gasstorage tanks storing a one years' reserve, 4. the installation of centralhigh-pressure natural gas pipelines transporting natural gas from theBuckow border to the Berlin GASAG premises. (BR)</TEXT></DOC>